       _d_._r_a_s_t_._a_r_r_o_w  is  designed to help users better visualize surface water
       flow direction, as indicated in an aspect raster map layer.  There  are
       two  ways to specify the aspect layer the program is to use.  The first
       is to display the aspect map layer on the graphics monitor before  run-
       ning  _d_._r_a_s_t_._a_r_r_o_w.  The second method involves setting the _m_a_p parame-
       ter to the name of the desired aspect map.  This allows the  arrows  to
       be drawn over any other maps already displayed on the graphics monitor.


       _d_._r_a_s_t_._a_r_r_o_w will draw an arrow over each displayed cell to indicate in
       which  direction  the  cell slopes.  An arrow can point in one of eight
